  <section id="m2m-trusted-summary">
    <h2>M2M_TRUSTED Summary</h2>
    <p>
      The single major addition in v2.1 is <strong>M2M_TRUSTED (level 6)</strong> — a fleet-scope machine identity
      issued exclusively by the Robot Registry Foundation. It solves the multi-owner fleet orchestration problem:
      today, a cloud management plane commanding a fleet of robots owned by different CREATORs would need a
      separate CREATOR-level token per owner. M2M_TRUSTED collapses this into a single RRF-issued token backed
      by explicit per-owner consent.
    </p>
    <p>
      Level 6 sits above CREATOR (5) not because machines should have more authority than humans in general,
      but because cross-fleet operations require cross-owner authority that no single CREATOR can delegate.
      The RRF acts as the trust anchor and consent aggregator, and every CREATOR retains individual veto power
      via consent revocation.
    </p>

    <h3>Role Table (v2.1)</h3>
